cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.HC. 

The paper applies deep convolutional networks for automated detection of fractures on spine CT images, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning models specifically could also place the paper under cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves medical imaging and could be relevant to the field of human-computer interaction, placing it under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
